Description: AbSolution is an interactive framework for the exploration and analysis 
    of adaptive immune receptor repertoire sequencing (AIRR-seq) data. It enables 
    large-scale computation and integrated analysis of sequence-derived features, 
    including physicochemical properties, amino acid descriptor sets, sequence motifs, 
    compositional patterns, and somatic hypermutation metrics. The application supports 
    multiscale analysis across sequences, clones, and repertoires, with interactive 
    visualizations and statistical feature selection. AbSolution also facilitates 
    reproducible research by enabling structured export of data, code, parameters, 
    and computational environments.
